ultrasound question how often during pregnancy can i have an ultrasound done every visit or does it hurt the baby is it expensive and that's why most people only have a few when should i get one done please don't tell me to ask the doctor because i will i want to know about your experiences though i'm wk d generally you only have one or two ultrasounds during your pregnancy if you are unsure when you conceived they will do one at your st visit you will have the nd between weeks at a specialist it is a more indepth ultrasound and they will check for any signs of birth defects measure the baby and will be able to tell you the gender if baby is being cooperative your doctor will not prescribe further ultrasounds and your insurance will not pay unless medically necessary if you have a history of high blood pressure diabetes develop either during your pregnancy the will do more if you are over they will do another towards the end of your pregnancy ultrasounds do not hurt the baby as far as cost the nd ultrasound i had at the specialists office with my st child was over i went to a different specialist with my nd pregnancy and it was over so yes it is expensive i have gest diabetes history of high blood pressure and i'm over so i get an ultrasound every month thank goodness for insurance good luck and congrats on your pregnancy Obstetrics Pregnancy Prenatal diagnosis Childbirth Miscarriage Urinary incontinence Prenatal care Birth weight Cephalic disorder Spina bifida Stroke Hypertension Turner syndrome Folic acid Medical ultrasonography Anencephaly In vitro fertilisation Premature birth Infertility Breastfeeding Diabetic retinopathy Midwifery Androgen insensitivity syndrome Intact dilation and extraction Stomach cancer Stillbirth Adoption Abortion Breech birth Coeliac disease Psoriasis Menstrual cycle Publicly funded medicine Traumatic brain injury Prostate cancer Postpartum depression Erectile dysfunction Ultrasound Guinea pig Insurance Medical record Fetus Polycystic ov